Personnel of the Nasarawa State Command of the Nigeria Defence and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC) attached to the Nasarawa State Pensions Bureau have manhandled two journalists in Lafia, the state capital. One of the victims, Rabiu Omaku, the correspondent of Universal Reporters, an online medium, said he was taking photographs of the list of pensioners pasted on the notice board when the information officer of the Bureau, Ibrahim Dawaya, directed personnel of the NSCDC to seize his phone and when he refused, they pounced on him and hit his head with the butt of the gun. The other journalist, Gambo Ahmed, of Peopleâ€™s Daily newspaper, sustained injury when he wanted to intervene in the matter. Both victims are currently receiving treatment at the Dalhatu Araf Specialist Hospital, Lafia. Meanwhile, the State Commandant of NSCDC, Mohammad Mahmoud-Fari, condemned the assault on the journalists and deployed intelligence personnel to investigate. The Chairman of the Correspondents Chapel of the Nigerian Union of Journalists (NUJ), Suleiman Abubakar, condemned the attack and called for more protection for journalists.